elements.title: Thomas Beck
elements.contents: ... that Thomas Beck designed a syphon for the Rangitata Diversion Race made of 723 concrete pipes each weighing 28 tons, with another pipe section used as an explosives store (pictured)?

elements.title: Stony Brook Railroad
elements.contents: ... that the Stony Brook Railroad was in business from 1845 to 2022, but never owned a single locomotive or ran a single train?

elements.title: Sonya Legg
elements.contents: ... that British oceanographer Sonya Legg has studied the South China Sea, where waves can be taller than 200 metres (660 ft)?

elements.title: Rudolf-Oetker-Halle
elements.contents: ... that the Rudolf-Oetker-Halle, the concert hall of Bielefeld, remains mostly unchanged from its completion in 1930?

elements.title: food psychology
elements.contents: ... that food psychology research has found that the COVID-19 pandemic led to both reduced and increased consumption of junk food among different geographical populations and educational backgrounds?

elements.title: Harry J. Karns
elements.contents: ... that the first tequila distillery in the United States was opened in 1936 in Nogales, Arizona, by Harry J. Karns, former Arizona state senator and Nogales mayor?

elements.title: right to resist
elements.contents: ... that 40 countries constitutionally recognize a right to resist the government under certain circumstances?

elements.title: Russ Hoogerhyde
elements.contents: ... that six-time American national archery champion Russ Hoogerhyde performed trick shots including shooting a cigarette from the lips of a spectator?
